# =============================================================================
# ROTEM SCRAPER SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 
# ROTEM CREDENTIALS SETUP:
# 1. Get your RotemNetWeb username and password from your Rotem account
# 2. Set ROTEM_USERNAME to your Rotem username
# 3. Set ROTEM_PASSWORD to your Rotem password
# 4. The scraper will use these credentials to login and collect data
# 5. Data will be scraped every 5 minutes automatically
# 6. ML analysis will run every hour on the collected data
#
# TESTING ROTEM SCRAPER:
# 1. Set your Rotem credentials above
# 2. Run: docker-compose exec backend python manage.py test_scraper
# 3. Check the logs for scraping results
# 4. View collected data in Django admin at /admin/
#
# =============================================================================
# EMAIL SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 
# GMAIL SETUP:
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on your Google account
# 2. Go to Google Account settings > Security > 2-Step Verification > App passwords
# 3. Generate an app password for "Mail"
# 4. Use your Gmail address as EMAIL_HOST_USER
# 5. Use the generated app password as EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD
#
# OUTLOOK SETUP:
# 1. Use your Outlook email address as EMAIL_HOST_USER
# 2. Use your regular Outlook password as EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD
# 3. Make sure "Less secure app access" is enabled (if using personal account)
#
# YAHOO SETUP:
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on your Yahoo account
# 2. Generate an app password for "Mail"
# 3. Use your Yahoo email address as EMAIL_HOST_USER
# 4. Use the generated app password as EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD
#
# CUSTOM SMTP:
# 1. Contact your hosting provider for SMTP settings
# 2. Use the provided SMTP server details
# 3. Use your email credentials
#
# =============================================================================
# TESTING EMAIL CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# To test your email configuration:
# 1. Update the email settings above
# 2. Run: docker-compose exec backend python manage.py send_daily_tasks --test --farm-id 1 --test-email your-email@example.com
# 3. Check your email inbox for the test message
#
# =============================================================================
# DAILY EMAIL SCHEDULE
# =============================================================================
# The system sends daily task reminder emails at 9:00 PM
# To set up automatic sending:
# 1. Run: ./setup_email_cron.sh
# 2. Or use: docker-compose -f docker-compose.email.yml up -d
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - Never commit this file to version control
# - Use strong, unique passwords
# - Enable 2FA on email accounts
# - Use app-specific passwords when available
# - Rotate passwords regularly
# - Monitor email sending logs for suspicious activity